  {
    "uid": "doi:10.2139/ssrn.6975018",
    "drop": false,
    "field": "management",
    "role": "object",
    "bullets": [
      "Analytical game-theoretic queueing model of AI-human handoffs in customer-facing service systems, with a firm setting a verification policy and strategic, delay-sensitive customers; no empirical data.",
      "Does not use a language model; it models generative AI agents whose answers carry unobservable hallucination risk, and derives equilibrium customer bypass and firm verification behavior.",
      "Shows an AI improvement trap where, above a hallucination-risk threshold, higher AI accuracy lowers effective throughput, though consumer surplus always rises, exposing firm-customer incentive misalignment."
    ],
